            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Full multicursor would be nice but for now, for `co...` you can use gbprod/substitute.nvim. `vim.keymap.set(\"n\", \"co\", require('substitute.range').word, { noremap = true })` gets you basically there. It uses the inbuilt `:s` command and its incremental preview so it looks pretty smooth.\r\n\r\n",
